{\\\\\\\"nodeType\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\":`Organization`\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"properties\\\\\\\": [{\\\\\\\"propertyName\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"propertyTypes\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"String\\\\\\\"]}]}, {\\\\\\\"nodeType\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\":`_GraphConfig`\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"properties\\\\\\\": [{\\\\\\\"propertyName\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"_classLabel\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"propertyTypes\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"String\\\\\\\"]}, {\\\\\\\"propertyName\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"_handleRDFTypes\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"propertyTypes\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"Integer\\\\\\\"]}, {\\\\\\\"propertyName\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"_subClassOfRel\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"propertyTypes\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"String\\\\\\\"]}, {\\\\\\\"propertyName\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"_handleMultival\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"propertyTypes\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"Integer\\\\\\\"]}, {\\\\\\\"propertyName\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"_objectPropertyLabel\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"propertyTypes\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"String\\\\\\\"]}, {\\\\\\\"propertyName\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"_rangeRel\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"propertyTypes\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"String\\\\\\\"]}, {\\\\\\\"propertyName\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"_domainRel\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"propertyTypes\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"String\\\\\\\"]}, {\\\\\\\"propertyName\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"_keepLangTag\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"propertyTypes\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"Boolean\\\\\\\"]}, {\\\\\\\"propertyName\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"_keepCustomDataTypes\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"propertyTypes\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"Boolean\\\\\\\"]}, {\\\\\\\"propertyName\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"_classNamePropName\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"propertyTypes\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"String\\\\\\\"]}, {\\\\\\\"propertyName\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"_handleVocabUris\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"propertyTypes\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"Integer\\\\\\\"]}, {\\\\\\\"propertyName\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"_applyNeo4jNaming\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"propertyTypes\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"Boolean\\\\\\\"]}, {\\\\\\\"propertyName\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"_relNamePropName\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"propertyTypes\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"String\\\\\\\"]}, {\\\\\\\"propertyName\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"_dataTypePropertyLabel\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"propertyTypes\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"String\\\\\\\"]}, {\\\\\\\"propertyName\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"_subPropertyOfRel\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"propertyTypes\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"String\\\\\\\"]}]}]\\\"}]\"],\"options\":{\"api_key\":{\"lc\":1,\"type\":\"secret\",\"id\":[\"GROQ_API_KEY\"]},\"model\":\"openai/gpt-oss-120b\",\"temperature\":0.7},\"response\":{\"response\":{\"generations\":[[{\"text\":\"**Graph Overview**\\n\\nThe Neo4j database contains a small, well‑structured knowledge graph that models **projects**, the **organizations** that own or develop them, the **locations** where they sit, and a few generic helper entities (Memory, Episodic, Community, Entity, and internal configuration).  \\n\\nBelow is a concise, human‑readable description of every node label (entity), its most important properties, indexes/constraints, and the relationship types that connect the entities.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. Node Labels (Entities)\\n\\n| Label | Typical Role | Key Properties (type) | Indexes | Uniqueness Constraints |\\n|-------|--------------|-----------------------|---------|------------------------|\\n| **Project** | A concrete project (e.g., a wind‑farm, solar plant, etc.) | `name` (String)  <br> `country` (String)  <br> `key_dates` (String)  <br> `status` (String)  <br> `capacity_MW` (Long/Double)  <br> `wind_capacity_MW` (Long)  <br> `technology` (String)  <br> `extracted_at` (DateTime)  <br> `region_raw` (String)  <br> `status_raw` (String)  <br> `milestone_2026` (String)  <br> `expected_commissioning_year` (Long)  <br> `bess_GWh` (Long/Double)  <br> `capacity` (String)  <br> `hydro_capacity_MW` (Double) | `name` <br> `uuid` <br> `name,summary,group_id` <br> `created_at` <br> `group_id` | **Two** uniqueness constraints: <br> • `(:Project {name})` <br> • `(:Project {name, country})` |\\n| **Organization** | Owner / developer of projects | `name` (String) | – | **Uniqueness** on `(:Organization {name})` |\\n| **Location** | Geographic place (city / region) | `name` (String) <br> `country` (String) | – | **Uniqueness** on `(:Location {name, country})` |\\n| **Community** | A grouping of entities (e.g., a user‑defined community) | `uuid` (String) <br> `name` (String) <br> `group_id` (String) | `uuid` <br> `name,group_id` <br> `group_id` | – |\\n| **Memory** | Generic “memory” node used by the system (e.g., episodic memory) | `name` (String) <br> `type` (String) <br> `observations` (String) | `name,type,observations` | – |\\n| **Episodic** | Time‑stamped episodic record | `group_id` (String) <br> `valid_at` (DateTime) <br> `created_at` (DateTime) <br> `content` (String) <br> `source` (String) <br> `source_description` (String) <br> `uuid` (String) | `group_id` <br> `valid_at` <br> `created_at` <br> `content,source,source_description,group_id` <br> `uuid` | – |\\n| **Entity** | Generic base label used for many “thing” nodes | (no explicit schema shown) | `name` <br> `uuid` <br> `name,summary,group_id` <br> `created_at` <br> `group_id` | – |\\n| **_GraphConfig** | Internal configuration for the graph (RDF mapping, etc.) | `_classLabel` (String) <br> `_handleRDFTypes` (Integer) <br> `_subClassOfRel` (String) <br> `_handleMultival` (Integer) <br> `_objectPropertyLabel` (String) <br> `_rangeRel` (String) <br> `_domainRel` (String) <br> `_keepLangTag` (Boolean) <br> `_keepCustomDataTypes` (Boolean) <br> `_classNamePropName` (String) <br> `_handleVocabUris` (Integer) <br> `_applyNeo4jNaming` (Boolean) <br> `_relNamePropName` (String) <br> `_dataTypePropertyLabel` (String) <br> `_subPropertyOfRel` (String) | – | – |\\n\\n*The schema query also listed a few generic indexes (`name`, `uuid`, etc.) that are present on several labels.*\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2. Relationship Types\\n\\n| Relationship | Direction (source → target) | Meaning |\\n|--------------|-----------------------------|---------|\\n| **OWNED_BY** | `Project → Organization` | The project is owned by the organization. |\\n| **LOCATED_IN** | `Project → Location` | Physical location of the project. |\\n| **EPC_BY** | `Project → Organization` | The organization is the EPC (Engineering, Procurement & Construction) contractor. |\\n| **DEVELOPED_BY** | `Project → Organization` | The organization is the developer of the project. |\\n| **HAS_MEMBER** | (generic) – used to link a Community to its members (e.g., Projects, Organizations, etc.). |\\n| **RELATES_TO** | (generic) – a flexible link for any two entities that have a contextual relation. |\\n| **MENTIONS** | (generic) – used when one node mentions another (e.g., a Memory mentions a Project). |\\n\\n*The first four relationships are the only ones that have explicit schema information (they appear in the visualization output). The remaining three (`HAS_MEMBER`, `RELATES_TO`, `MENTIONS`) exist in the DB but have no defined property schema.*\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3. Summary of Constraints & Indexes\\n\\n* **Uniqueness constraints** ensure that the combination of key attributes is unique across the graph:  \\n  * `Project.name`  \\n  * `Project.{name, country}`  \\n  * `Organization.name`  \\n  * `Location.{name, country}`  \\n\\n* **Indexes** (mostly for fast lookup) are defined on common identifier fields such as `name`, `uuid`, and composite fields like `name,summary,group_id`.  \\n\\nThese constraints and indexes are automatically enforced by Neo4j, guaranteeing data integrity for the core entities.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4. How the Graph Is Typically Used\\n\\n* **Project‑centric queries** – find all projects owned, developed, or EPC‑by a given organization, or locate them in a country/location.  \\n* **Community‑based grouping** – a Community can aggregate Projects, Organizations, Locations, etc., via `HAS_MEMBER`.  \\n* **Memory / Episodic** – the system stores observations, events, or notes (Memory/Episodic) that can be linked to any entity using generic relationships (`MENTIONS`, `RELATES_TO`).  \\n* **Configuration** – `_GraphConfig` stores internal RDF‑mapping metadata; it is not part of the domain model but needed for the graph‑engine.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 5. Quick Example Queries (for reference)\\n\\n```cypher\\n// 1️⃣ All projects in Germany together with their owners and locations\\nMATCH (p:Project)-[:OWNED_BY]->(o:Organization),\\n      (p)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(l:Location {country: 'Germany'})\\nRETURN p.name AS project, o.name AS owner, l.name AS city;\\n\\n// 2️⃣ All organizations that develop at least one wind project\\nMATCH (p:Project {technology: 'Wind'})-[:DEVELOPED_BY]->(org:Organization)\\nRETURN DISTINCT org.name;\\n\\n// 3️⃣ Find memories that mention a specific project\\nMATCH (m:Memory)-[:MENTIONS]->(p:Project {name: 'Solar Farm X'})\\nRETURN m;\\n```\\n\\nThese examples illustrate the typical navigation patterns enabled by the schema described above.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Final Note\\n\\nThe graph is compact but well‑structured: the **Project** label carries the richest set of domain‑specific attributes, while **Organization**, **Location**, and **Community** provide the contextual scaffolding. Generic nodes (Memory, Episodic, Entity) and the internal `_GraphConfig` support auxiliary functionality such as logging, reasoning, and configuration. All relationships are clearly typed, and key constraints guarantee that duplicate entities cannot be created inadvertently.\",\"generationInfo\":{\"finish_reason\":\"stop\"}}]]},\"tokenUsage\":{\"completionTokens\":2006,\"promptTokens\":4551,\"totalTokens\":6557}}}"}}
