-san-pedro-y-san-javier-creara-2200-empleos.`{{cite web}}`: Check `|url=` value (help); Missing or empty `|title=` (help) 4.   ↑https://murciaplaza.com/la-mega-planta-solar-de-total-y-soltec-en-murcia-san-pedro-y-san-javier-creara-2200-empleos https://murciaplaza.com/la-mega-planta-solar-de-total-y-soltec-en-murcia-san-pedro-y-san-javier-creara-2200-empleos, https://murciaplaza.com/la-mega-planta-solar-de-total-y-soltec-en-murcia-san-pedro-y-san-javier-creara-2200-empleos.`{{cite web}}`: Check `|url=` value (help); Missing or empty `|title=` (help) title=Luminora_solar_farm&oldid=888661\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.72042775,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://newsroom.ferrovial.com/en-us/press-releases/ferrovial-to-build-three-photovoltaic-plants-in-murcia-spain-with-capacity-to-supply-30500-homes/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Ferrovial to build three photovoltaic plants in Murcia, Spain ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"TheLuminora Solar Tresplant, located in the municipalities ofMurciaand Torre Pacheco, will have a capacity of 95 MWp. Ferrovial will manage the design\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.65861565,\\\"raw_content\\\":null}],\\\"response_time\\\":1.69,\\\"request_id\\\":\\\"b7e817da-b8db-4ad3-9587-2b4a7201b08b\\\"}]\\nAI: \\nTool: [{\\\"query\\\":\\\"Entrenúcleos solar park Plenitude Eni Seville Andalusia solar project\\\",\\\"follow_up_questions\\\":null,\\\"answer\\\":\\\"The Entrenúcleos solar park in Andalusia, Spain, is a 200 MW project by Plenitude, expected to start operations in 2026. It will generate over 435 GWh annually. The project is located in Dos Hermanas and Coria del Río.\\\",\\\"images\\\":[],\\\"results\\\":[{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.eni.com/en-IT/media/press-release/2025/07/plenitude-begins-construction-new-200-mw-solar-park-spain.html\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Plenitude begins construction of a new 200 MW solar park in Spain\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The Entrenúcleos project, located between Dos Hermanas and Coria del Río (Seville, Andalusia), is expected to begin operations in 2026 and generate more than\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.87605256,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://energynews.pro/en/plenitude-starts-200-mw-solar-park-in-andalusia-for-2026/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Plenitude starts 200 MW solar park in Andalusia for 2026\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Italian group Plenitude has begun building Entrenúcleos, a 200 MW photovoltaic plant near Seville, set to deliver more than 435 GWh a year from 2026.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.8755427,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://energy-analytics-institute.org/2025/07/03/plenitude-starts-construction-of-new-200-mw-solar-park-in-spain-andalusia/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Plenitude starts construction of new 200 MW solar park in Spain ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"... Entrenúcleos, a new 200 MW photovoltaic project located in the municipalities of Dos Hermanas and Coria del Río, in the province of Seville (Andalusia).\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.87113565,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.akm.ru/eng/news/italian-subsidiary-eni-plenitude-expands-business-in-spain/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Italian subsidiary Eni Plenitude expands business in Spain - AK&M\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The Entrenúcleos project, which will install 326,000 solar panels, is located in the municipalities of Dos Hermanas and Coria del Río in the province of Seville\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.8622012,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.power-technology.com/news/plenitude-200mw-pv-project-spain/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Plenitude begins construction of 200MW PV project in Spain\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Entrenúcleos solar park is designed to consist of four plants: Granville, Killington, Plumlee and Rickwood.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.79369855,\\\"raw_content\\\":null}],\\\"response_time\\\":0.98,\\\"request_id\\\":\\\"d4766a8f-16fb-45b3-97b9-00ca5e9f3b4d\\\"}]\\nAI: **Step 2: Filter URLs and extract most relevant sources**\\n\\nLet me fetch the most relevant sources for each project:\\n\\n**Step 3: Fetch markdown content**\\nTool: [{\\\"type\\\":\\\"text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Contents of https://soltec.com/en/press-room/totalenergies-soltec-obtain-construction-authorization-200-mw-project-murcia/:\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nSoltec obtain construction authorization for a 200 MW\\\\n\\\\nUSAContactEN EnglishProjectsPress RoomOur purposeA company with a clear purpose: creating a 100% sustainable world is not an easy task.Our businessCommitment to vertical integration through an integrated, sustainable and innovative business model.Join this revolutionWe work to create innovative technological solutions to improve the lives of people and the world.Work with usAll about who we arePhotovoltaic developmentExperience and innovation to promote the development of sustainable photovoltaic projects and integrated with the environment.Asset ManagementWe increase efficiency and get the best performance from each project through effective asset management.ProductsSFOneXSFOneSF7SFOne USSF7 US4×4AgrovoltaicServicesConstructionSolmateAll about solutionsOur strategyA business model based on growth, respect for the environment and improving people's lives.Supply ChainAn agile, flexible and sustainable service network with local suppliers aligned with our values.EcovoltaicsThe photovoltaic plants of now and tomorrow. Minimum environmental impact and maximum social benefit.Sustainability certificationsSustainability indexes and ratings, as well as our certifications.All about sustainabilitySoltec InnovationsA specialized team with the sole objective of innovating against climate change.AuroraWe are committed to emerging companies with technological solutions that help us promote renewable energy.Lab\\\\n\\\\nDiscover Lab\\\\n\\\\nHarnessing smart solar tracking: Advanced algorithms for hail protectionDiscover our whitepaper on how to take advantage of smart solar tracking for hail protection.All about innovationInvestor kitWhy invest in Soltec?Stock InformationAnalyst’ OpinionInvestor CalendarFinancial informationAnnual reportsQuarterly financial informationPresentationsNotifications sent to CNMVCorporate governanceBoard of DirectorsGeneral Shareholders ́ MeetingCorporate regulations and policiesAnnual reportsAll about shareholders and investors\\\\n\\\\n* Home\\\\n* Press Room\\\\n* New\\\\n6 November 2023\\\\n# TotalEnergies and Soltec obtain construction authorization for a 200 MW project in Murcia\\\\n\\\\n* The plant will prevent the emission of over 3 million tons of CO2 into the atmosphere over its 30-year lifespan\\\\n* The plant, with construction set to begin in 2024, will create more than 2,200 jobs, both direct and indirect, during its construction phase\\\\n\\\\nThe Luminora Solar Dos photovoltaic project, with a capacity of 200 MW, developed by TotalEnergies, a multi-energy company, and Soltec, a vertically integrated photovoltaic company, in the Region of Murcia has received Administrative Construction Authorization.\\\\n\\\\nThe project, located in the municipality of Murcia, features 337,174 bifacial photovoltaic modules and 5,341 SF7 solar trackers, supplied by Soltec, and will generate enough electricity to cover the estimated annual consumption of over 114,000 households. Furthermore, the plant will prevent the emission of more than 3 million tons of CO2 into the atmosphere each year during its 30-year lifespan.\\\\n\\\\nThe plant, with construction set to begin in 2024 and involving the participation of Soltec, will create more than 2,200 direct and indirect jobs during its construction phase. The total investment for the project amounts to approximately 100 million euros.\\\\n\\\\nIn the project’s design, both companies have implemented various environmental protection measures as social and environmental guarantees included in the Environmental and Landscape Integration Plan of the project. In order to preserve biodiversity, prior flora surveys have been conducted, and measures such as the installation of vegetative screens, replanting of native species, and anti-collision and electrocution measures have been implemented to protect avifauna. Similarly, the use of the territory by the Bonelli’s eagle and the golden eagle has been monitored, with one of these species being GPS-GSM tagged to monitor its movements and enhance knowledge of its evolution in coordination with the environmental authority of the autonomous community.\\\\n\\\\nIn terms of local development, the project includes initiatives such as the installation of self-consumption solutions in the Red Cross headquarters and in several public buildings belonging to the Murcia City Council, as well as measures aimed at enabling the residents of nearby towns to reduce their energy bills or to participate economically in the project.\\\\n\\\\nYago Mancebo, General Manager of TotalEnergies Renewables Spain, said that “our company has made a firm commitment to promote renewable energy in the Region of Murcia. Obtaining the construction permit for this project is a major step forward that will allow us to contribute both to the decarbonization of the environment and to the development of local economies, all while ensuring the protection of the biodiversity of the surrounding area”.\\\\n\\\\n“We are very proud to continue working to make our region a more sustainable place while contr\\\\n\\\\n<error>Content truncated. Call the fetch tool with a start_index of 5000 to get more content.</error>\\\"}]\"],\"options\":{\"api_key\":{\"lc\":1,\"type\":\"secret\",\"id\":[\"GROQ_API_KEY\"]},\"model\":\"moonshotai/kimi-k2-instruct-0905\",\"temperature\":0.7},\"response\":{\"response\":{\"generations\":[[{\"text\":\"\",\"generationInfo\":{\"finish_reason\":\"tool_calls\"}}]]},\"tokenUsage\":{\"completionTokens\":53,\"promptTokens\":4019,\"totalTokens\":4072}}}"}}
